  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Ellicott's Commentary for English Readers",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(21, 22) These two verses contain one statement, viz :—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "The sons of Laadan, i.e., The sons of the Gershonite belonging to Laadan, the heads of the houses of Laadan the Gershonite, Jehieli,",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " that is, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "the sons of Kehieli, Zetham, and Joel his brother, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "were ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "over the treasures of the house of Jehovah.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " In other words, Zetham and Joel the chiefs of the clan Jehiel, which was the leading house of the Laadanite branch of Gershon, had charge of the Temple stores. (Comp. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1Chronicles 23:7-8",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".) Jehieli looks like the gentilic form of Jehiel, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "the Jehielite.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
